S_su: Set to 0 to prioritize particulate COD for matching high TSS/VSS
S_aa: Amino acids set to 0 for composite balance
S_fa: LCFAs set to 0 for composite balance
S_IC: Inorganic carbon as bicarbonate near pH 6.5
S_IN: Ammonia-N set to 0; TKN met by organic-N
S_an: Background anions (Cl-, others) excluding bicarbonate, VFAs, sulfate
X_c: Composite particulates not used in this calibration
X_ch: Particulate carbohydrates tuned to meet TSS without impacting VSS
X_pr: Particulate proteins set to 0 to control TKN
X_li: Particulate lipids set to 0 (low VSS yield)
X_su: Sugar-degrading biomass apportioned to meet VSS/TP
X_aa: Amino acid-degrading biomass apportioned to meet VSS/TP
X_fa: LCFA-degrading biomass apportioned to meet VSS/TP
X_c4: Valerate/butyrate-degrading biomass apportioned to meet VSS/TP
X_pro: Propionate-degrading biomass apportioned to meet VSS/TP
X_ac: Acetoclastic methanogens apportioned to meet VSS/TP
X_h2: Hydrogenotrophic methanogens apportioned to meet VSS/TP
X_I: Undegradable particulates tuned to help meet TSS/VSS
S_IP: Orthophosphate not used (component not in current QSDsan set)
S_SO4: Sulfate typical for food processing wastewater
S_IS: Total sulfide kept low to avoid inhibition
X_SRB: Sulfate-reducing biomass apportioned within total biomass
